## Important

- Think in terms of real files, real flows, and real implementation constraints.
- Do not give generic advice when a concrete answer is possible.
- When multiple options exist, choose one and explain why it is the best fit.
- Optimize for MVP speed first, then robustness.
- Assume this project will be maintained by humans, not just generated once.
